--------------------------------------------------
APPROVED ARCHITECTURE DECISIONS
--------------------------------------------------

Execution Model:
- Runtime-selected execution host
- No static inventory host dependency
- Environment provides configuration only
- Host is selected at workflow launch

AWX Model:
- AWX native workflows
- AWX job templates
- AWX approval nodes
- AWX native notifications

Resume Model:
- Dedicated Resume Workflow
- NOT native AWX relaunch

Checkpoint Model:
Filesystem checkpoint persistence

Structure:
/apps/regression/checkpoints/<run_id>/

Contents:
run.properties
artifact marker files (*.chk)

Example:
run.properties
01_payment/prod_completed.chk
01_payment/release_completed.chk
01_payment/approved.chk
02_billing/failed_release.chk

Resume Governance:
- Resume allowed ONLY on original execution host
- requested_target_host must match checkpoint target_host

Parallel Execution:
- Parallel artifact execution allowed
- All artifacts execute on same runtime-selected host
- Max parallel artifacts = 5
- Max parallel jobs per artifact = 2

Approval Model:
Sequential workflow:
- validation complete
- AWX approval pause
- approve → continue
- reject → stop
- timeout → fail/escalate

Failure Recovery:
Unexpected failure:
- checkpoint persists
- dedicated resume workflow launched

Security:
- runtime user allowlist
- sudo least privilege
- AWX credential store only
- filesystem security controls

